ht on the role organizations themselves may play in fostering such criminal behavior. The volume considers psychological factors involved in theft and fraud, workplace violence, employee discrimination, and sexual harassment. It also analyses a number of variables which can influence such behavior including employee personality, employee emotional processes, experience of occupational stress, organizational culture, organizational injustice, and human resource management practices. The book will be of core interest to those interested in the psychology and sociology of work, organizational behavior, and human resource management.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEmployee crimesxPsychological aspects. 0aProblem employeesxPsychology. 0aPsychology, Industrial. 0aViolence in the workplace. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh1 aAshkanasy, Neal M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarney, Chet E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenson, Philip G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCropanzano, Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElias, Steven M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElias, Steven M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGibson, Lindsey A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Sharon L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Ricky W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGross, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaines, Brandon Hill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanley, Glennis M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc